{{Infobox university |name = Academy of Performing Arts in Bratislava |native_name = Vysoká škola múzických umení v Bratislave (VŠMU) |image = Zochova_1.jpg |image_name = |image_size = |image_alt = |caption = |latin_name = |motto = |mottoeng = |established = 1949 |closed = |type = |affiliation = |endowment = |officer_in_charge = |chairman = |chancellor = |president = |vice-president = |superintendent = |provost = |vice_chancellor = |rector = |principal = |dean = |director = |head_label = |head = |faculty = |staff = |students = |undergrad = |postgrad = |doctoral = |other = |city = [[Bratislava]] |state = |province = |country = {{flagicon|Slovakia}} [[Slovakia]] |coor = |campus = |former_names = |free_label = |free = |sports = |colors = |colours = |nickname = |mascot = |athletics = |affiliations = |website = http://www.vsmu.sk/ |logo = |footnotes = }}
The '''Academy of Performing Arts in Bratislava''' ({{lang-sk|Vysoká škola múzických umení v Bratislave}}, abbr. VŠMU) is a university founded on June 9, 1949. <gallery> File:Zochova_1.jpg </gallery> The university consists of three faculties: *''Theatre Faculty'' (Acting, Directing, Dramaturgy, Stage and Costume Design, Puppetry, Theatre Theory, Theatre Management) *''Faculty of Film and Television'' (Directing, Documentary, Dramaturgy and Scriptwriting, Photography and Picture Composition, Animation, Editing, Sound Design, Production, Management and Business Studies, Film and TV Theory) *''Faculty of Music and Dance'' (Composition, Orchestra Conducting, Theory of Music, Voice, Opera Directing, Instrumental Playing (16 majors), Dance (6 majors))
==Notable alumni== *[[Adriana Kučerová]], soprano<ref>"[http://www.snd.sk/?detail-2&meno=kucerova-adriana Adriana Kučerová]." ([https://www.webcitation.org/6BAWXGANZ?url=http://www.snd.sk/?detail-2%26meno%3Dkucerova-adriana Archive]) {{sk icon}} [[Slovak National Theatre]]. Retrieved on 4 October 2012. "Štúdia absolvovala na j VŠMU v Bratislave[...]"</ref> *[[Marek Maďarič]], Slovak Minister of Culture<ref>{{cite web|title=Marek Madaric|url=http://www.vlada.gov.sk/marek-madaric/|publisher=Government of Slovakia|accessdate=20 December 2012}}</ref> *[[Alexander Moyzes]], composer *[[Ján Cikker]], composer *[[Jolana Fogašová]], soprano *[[Ľudovít Rajter]], composer *[[Frico Kafenda]], composer *[[Ladislav Slovák]], conductor *[[Ivan Hrušovský]], composer *[[Pavol Gábor]], tenor *[[Štefan Hoza]], tenor *[[Bohdan Warchal]], violinist *[[Miroslav Dvorský]], tenor *[[Zuzana Piussi]] aka Susan Piussi, filmmaker *[[Juraj Nvota]], theatre and film director *[[Martin Šulík]], film director *[[Emília Vášáryová]], actress *[[Tatiana Pauhofová]], actress *[[Martin Kollar]], photographer<ref>"[https://web.archive.org/web/20151219002303/http://www.getxophoto.com/en/archive/festival-2010/authors-2010/martin-kollar/ Authors 2010: Martin Kollar: Nothing Special]", Getxophoto.</ref> *[[Sylvia Čápová-Vizváry]], pianist<ref>{{cite web|last=Jancik|first=Filip|title=Curriculum Vitae|url=http://www.sylviacapova-vizvary.com/biography.html|work=Sylvia Čápová - Vizváry|accessdate=22 October 2017|year=2013}}</ref> *[[:it:Kristína Mravcová?veaction=edit&section=1|Kristína Mravcová]], actress *[[Lucia Popp]], soprano *[[Edita Gruberová]], soprano
