{{italic title}}
'''''Athuru Mithuru''''' is a [[preschool]] education paper in [[Sri Lanka]] which prints in [[Sinhala language]] monthly. ''Athuru Mithuru'' is the most popular preschool education paper in Sri Lanka which runs according to the pre-school curriculum.{{citation needed|date=February 2013}}
It is published by the [[Associated Newspapers of Ceylon Limited]] (Lake House), a government-owned company. 
The education paper commenced publishing on 1 May 2012. ''Athuru Mithuru'' is written as a [[tabloid (newspaper format)|tabloid]] size, with colorful drawings. It includes preschool activities, drawings, poems, stories and competitions.

The current editor-in-chief of the paper is Anoma Gangoda while Gunapala Jayalath is the sub-editor. The circulation is close to 100,000 and sales are managed by Dinesh De Alwis. ''Athuru Mithuru'' is distributed to the entire island by the Lake House Circulation Department headed by Sunil Sendanayake.

