The '''Metro Toronto Elementary Teacher's strike''' was a month-long labour dispute that saw nearly 10,000 elementary teachers in Metro [[Toronto]], [[Ontario]], Canada, walk off the job in a bid to achieve more preparation time. The strike ran from 21 September<ref>[https://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/thestar/doc/435666847.html?FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:FT&type=current&date=Oct+5%2C+1987&author=Robert+Brehl+Toronto+Star&pub=Toronto+Star&edition=&startpage=&desc=Kids+may+be+harmed+by+teachers%27+strike+psychologist+says Kids may be harmed by teachers' strike psychologist says]. ''[[Toronto Star]]'', October 5, 1987. Page A5.</ref> to 18 October 1987.<ref>[https://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/thestar/doc/435657688.html?FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:FT&type=current&date=Oct+18%2C+1987&author=Kelly+Toughill+and+Paul+Bilodeau+Toronto+Star&pub=Toronto+Star&edition=&startpage=&desc=Strike%27s+over%21+157%2C000+kids+back+in+class+on+Monday Strike's over! 157,000 kids back in class on Monday]. ''[[Toronto Star]]'', October 18, 1987. Page A1.</ref>

